    "actor_description": "It hits fast-like something unclenches behind my ribs. A laugh starts before I've decided to make one, and the air in my lungs turns light. For a second the world is simple. My face warms, my eyes sting with that clean, ridiculous brightness, and I can feel my body lean toward the moment instead of bracing away from it. I try to hold it in-out of habit-and it slips past anyway: the grin, the breath I didn't realize I'd been rationing, the small rush of yes. I'm still me. Nothing's solved. But right now my nervous system believes in good news.",
    "description_text": "{actor} brightens all at once-like a light turning on behind their eyes. A grin breaks free, quick and unguarded, and a short laugh slips out before they can smooth it down. Their shoulders ease, posture loosening, as if something in them finally gave permission to feel good.",
